{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775846980109,"sessionID":"ses_28745be05ffeTzMz0TdWYlVggx","part":{"id":"prt_d78ba6f730010PUTc68ekeyRNI","messageID":"msg_d78ba6695001WMDfb24Zgke0Vk","sessionID":"ses_28745be05ffeTzMz0TdWYlVggx","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_e2b09f8703054660a482edb0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/workloadmanager/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/workloadmanager/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-008: Sandbox GC 定时清理机制 (Sandbox GC Timing Cleanup Mechanism)\n2: \n3: - **AR ID**: AR-008\n4: - **Module**: pkg/workloadmanager\n5: - **Language**: Go\n6: - **Size**: S\n7: - **Status**: ST-1 Completed\n8: \n9: ## 1. Overview\n10: \n11: The Sandbox GC (Garbage Collection) mechanism provides automatic periodic cleanup of expired sandboxes in the workloadmanager module. This feature extends the existing expiration logic in `expiration.go` by adding a scheduled GC worker that proactively identifies and removes expired resources, ensuring cluster resources are efficiently managed.\n12: \n13: ## 2. Architecture\n14: \n15: ### 2.1 Component Structure\n16: \n17: ```\n18: pkg/workloadmanager/\n19: ├── client.go              # Kubernetes client initialization (existing)\n20: ├── service.go             # WorkloadManager interface (existing)\n21: ├── server.go              # HTTP server (existing)\n22: ├── types.go               # Request/Response types (existing)\n23: ├── expiration.go          # Expiration detection logic (existing)\n24: ├── cleanup.go             # Resource cleanup handlers (existing)\n25: ├── gc.go                  # NEW: GC worker and scheduler\n26: ├── gc_test.go             # NEW: GC unit tests\n27: └── design.md              # This design document\n28: ```\n29: \n30: ### 2.2 Architecture Diagram\n31: \n32: ```\n33: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n34: │                     GC Scheduler                             │\n35: │              (golang.org/x/time/rate Ticker)                │\n36: └─────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────────────┘\n37:                       │\n38:                       ▼\n39: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n40: │                    GC Worker                                 │\n41: │  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐   │\n42: │  │ ListExpired │→ │ Check State │→ │ Execute Delete  │   │\n43: │  │ Sandboxes   │  │ (finalizers)│  │ (with cleanup)  │   │\n44: │  └─────────────┘  └─────────────┘  └─────────────────┘   │\n45: └─────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────────────┘\n46:                       │\n47:                       ▼\n48: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n49: │              WorkloadManager Service                         │\n50: │    (Expiration + Cleanup + Deletion operations)            │\n51: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n52: ```\n53: \n54: ## 3. Data Structures\n55: \n56: ### 3.1 GC Configuration\n57: \n58: ```go\n59: // GCConfig defines the garbage collection configuration.\n60: type GCConfig struct {\n61:     // Interval is the time between GC cycles.\n62:     Interval time.Duration\n63:     \n64:     // BatchSize is the maximum number of sandboxes to process per cycle.\n65:     BatchSize int\n66:     \n67:     // MaxConcurrentDeletes is the maximum number of concurrent delete operations.\n68:     MaxConcurrentDeletes int\n69:     \n70:     // GracePeriod is the time to wait after deletion timestamp before forcing delete.\n71:     GracePeriod time.Duration\n72:     \n73:     // EnableMetrics enables metrics collection.\n74:     EnableMetrics bool\n75: }\n76: \n77: // DefaultGCConfig returns the default GC configuration.\n78: func DefaultGCConfig() *GCConfig {\n79:     return &GCConfig{\n80:         Interval:             5 * time.Minute,\n81:         BatchSize:            50,\n82:         MaxConcurrentDeletes: 10,\n83:         GracePeriod:          30 * time.Second,\n84:         EnableMetrics:        true,\n85:     }\n86: }\n87: ```\n88: \n89: ### 3.2 GC Worker\n90: \n91: ```go\n92: // GCWorker performs periodic garbage collection of expired sandboxes.\n93: type GCWorker struct {\n94:     client        versioned.Interface\n95:     k8sClient     *kubernetes.Clientset\n96:     config        *GCConfig\n97:     stopCh        chan struct{}\n98:     cleanupMgr    *CleanupManager\n99:     expirationChecker *ExpirationChecker\n100: }\n101: \n102: // NewGCWorker creates a new GC worker instance.\n103: func NewGCWorker(\n104:     client versioned.Interface,\n105:     k8sClient *kubernetes.Clientset,\n106:     config *GCConfig,\n107: ) *GCWorker {\n108:     if config == nil {\n109:         config = DefaultGCConfig()\n110:     }\n111:     \n112:     return &GCWorker{\n113:         client:             client,\n114:         k8sClient:          k8sClient,\n115:         config:             config,\n116:         stopCh:             make(chan struct{}),\n117:         cleanupMgr:         NewCleanupManager(k8sClient),\n118:         expirationChecker:  NewExpirationChecker(nil),\n119:     }\n120: }\n121: ```\n122: \n123: ### 3.3 GC Result\n124: \n125: ```go\n126: // GCResult contains the results of a GC cycle.\n127: type GCResult struct {\n128:     // ScannedCount is the number of sandboxes scanned.\n129:     ScannedCount int `json:\"scannedCount\"`\n130:     \n131:     // ExpiredCount is the number of sandboxes identified as expired.\n132:     ExpiredCount int `json:\"expiredCount\"`\n133:     \n134:     // DeletedCount is the number of sandboxes successfully deleted.\n135:     DeletedCount int `json:\"deletedCount\"`\n136:     \n137:     // FailedCount is the number of sandboxes that failed to delete.\n138:     FailedCount int `json:\"failedCount\"`\n139:     \n140:     // Duration is the time taken for the GC cycle.\n141:     Duration time.Duration `json:\"duration\"`\n142:     \n143:     // Errors contains any errors encountered during the cycle.\n144:     Errors []string `json:\"errors,omitempty\"`\n145: }\n146: ```\n147: \n148: ### 3.4 GC Statistics\n149: \n150: ```go\n151: // GCStats holds garbage collection statistics.\n152: type GCStats struct {\n153:     // TotalCycles is the total number of GC cycles run.\n154:     TotalCycles int64\n155:     \n156:     // TotalDeleted is the total number of sandboxes deleted.\n157:     TotalDeleted int64\n158:     \n159:     // TotalFailed is the total number of deletions that failed.\n160:     TotalFailed int64\n161:     \n162:     // LastRunTime is the time of the last GC run.\n163:     LastRunTime *metav1.Time\n164:     \n165:     // LastResult contains the result of the last GC cycle.\n166:     LastResult *GCResult\n167: }\n168: ```\n169: \n170: ## 4. API Contracts\n171: \n172: ### 4.1 GC Control Endpoints\n173: \n174: | Operation | Method | Resource Path | Description |\n175: |-----------|--------|---------------|-------------|\n176: | Trigger GC | POST | /api/v1/gc/trigger | Manually trigger a GC cycle |\n177: | Get GC Status | GET | /api/v1/gc/status | Get GC worker status and statistics |\n178: | Update GC Config | PUT | /api/v1/gc/config | Update GC configuration |\n179: \n180: ### 4.2 GC Response Types\n181: \n182: ```go\n183: // GCTriggerResponse is the response to a GC trigger request.\n184: type GCTriggerResponse struct {\n185:     // Started indicates whether the GC cycle was started.\n186:     Started bool `json:\"started\"`\n187:     \n188:     // Message provides additional information.\n189:     Message string `json:\"message\"`\n190: }\n191: \n192: // GCStatusResponse is the response to a GC status request.\n193: type GCStatusResponse struct {\n194:     // Running indicates if GC worker is running.\n195:     Running bool `json:\"running\"`\n196:     \n197:     // Config contains the current GC configuration.\n198:     Config *GCConfig `json:\"config\"`\n199:     \n200:     // Stats contains GC statistics.\n201:     Stats *GCStats `json:\"stats\"`\n202:     \n203:     // LastError contains the last error encountered.\n204:     LastError string `json:\"lastError,omitempty\"`\n205: }\n206: \n207: // GCConfigUpdateRequest is a request to update GC configuration.\n208: type GCConfigUpdateRequest struct {\n209:     // Interval is the new interval between GC cycles.\n210:     Interval string `json:\"interval,omitempty\"`\n211:     \n212:     // BatchSize is the new batch size.\n213:     BatchSize *int `json:\"batchSize,omitempty\"`\n214:     \n215:     // MaxConcurrentDeletes is the new max concurrent deletes.\n216:     MaxConcurrentDeletes *int `json:\"maxConcurrentDeletes,omitempty\"`\n217:     \n218:     // GracePeriod is the new grace period.\n219:     GracePeriod string `json:\"gracePeriod,omitempty\"`\n220: }\n221: ```\n222: \n223: ## 5. Implementation Details\n224: \n225: ### 5.1 GC Worker Lifecycle\n226: \n227: ```go\n228: // Start begins the GC worker.\n229: func (g *GCWorker) Start(ctx context.Context) {\n230:     klog.InfoS(\"Starting GC worker\", \"interval\", g.config.Interval)\n231:     \n232:     ticker := time.NewTicker(g.config.Interval)\n233:     defer ticker.Stop()\n234:     \n235:     for {\n236:         select {\n237:         case <-ctx.Done():\n238:             klog.InfoS(\"GC worker stopping due to context cancellation\")\n239:             return\n240:         case <-g.stopCh:\n241:             klog.InfoS(\"GC worker stopping\")\n242:             return\n243:         case <-ticker.C:\n244:             g.runGCCycle(ctx)\n245:         }\n246:     }\n247: }\n248: \n249: // Stop stops the GC worker.\n250: func (g *GCWorker) Stop() {\n251:     close(g.stopCh)\n252: }\n253: ```\n254: \n255: ### 5.2 GC Cycle Execution\n256: \n257: ```go\n258: // runGCCycle executes a single garbage collection cycle.\n259: func (g *GCWorker) runGCCycle(ctx context.Context) {\n260:     startTime := time.Now()\n261:     result := &GCResult{}\n262:     \n263:     klog.V(4).InfoS(\"Starting GC cycle\")\n264:     \n265:     namespaces, err := g.getNamespaces(ctx)\n266:     if err != nil {\n267:         klog.ErrorS(err, \"Failed to get namespaces\")\n268:         result.Errors = append(result.Errors, err.Error())\n269:         g.recordGCResult(result, startTime)\n270:         return\n271:     }\n272:     \n273:     result.ScannedCount = len(namespaces)\n274:     \n275:     for _, ns := range namespaces {\n276:         if err := g.processNamespace(ctx, ns, result); err != nil {\n277:             klog.ErrorS(err, \"Failed to process namespace\", \"namespace\", ns)\n278:             result.Errors = append(result.Errors, fmt.Sprintf(\"%s: %v\", ns, err))\n279:         }\n280:         \n281:         if result.ScannedCount >= g.config.BatchSize {\n282:             klog.V(4).InfoS(\"Batch size reached\", \"scanned\", result.ScannedCount)\n283:             break\n284:         }\n285:     }\n286:     \n287:     result.Duration = time.Since(startTime)\n288:     g.recordGCResult(result, startTime)\n289:     \n290:     klog.InfoS(\"GC cycle completed\",\n291:         \"scanned\", result.ScannedCount,\n292:         \"expired\", result.ExpiredCount,\n293:         \"deleted\", result.DeletedCount,\n294:         \"failed\", result.FailedCount,\n295:         \"duration\", result.Duration)\n296: }\n297: ```\n298: \n299: ### 5.3 Namespace Processing\n300: \n301: ```go\n302: // processNamespace processes expired sandboxes in a namespace.\n303: func (g *GCWorker) processNamespace(ctx context.Context, namespace string, result *GCResult) error {\n304:     // List AgentRuntimes\n305:     arList, err := g.client.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).List(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{})\n306:     if err != nil {\n307:         return fmt.Errorf(\"failed to list agentruntimes: %w\", err)\n308:     }\n309:     \n310:     // List CodeInterpreters\n311:     ciList, err := g.client.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(namespace).List(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{})\n312:     if err != nil {\n313:         return fmt.Errorf(\"failed to list codeinterpreters: %w\", err)\n314:     }\n315:     \n316:     // Check each AgentRuntime for expiration\n317:     for i := range arList.Items {\n318:         ar := &arList.Items[i]\n319:         result.ScannedCount++\n320:         \n321:         if g.isExpired(ar) {\n322:             result.ExpiredCount++\n323:             if err := g.deleteAgentRuntime(ctx, namespace, ar.Name); err != nil {\n324:                 result.FailedCount++\n325:                 result.Errors = append(result.Errors, fmt.Sprintf(\"agentruntime/%s: %v\", ar.Name, err))\n326:                 klog.ErrorS(err, \"Failed to delete expired agentruntime\", \"name\", ar.Name)\n327:             } else {\n328:                 result.DeletedCount++\n329:             }\n330:         }\n331:     }\n332:     \n333:     // Check each CodeInterpreter for expiration\n334:     for i := range ciList.Items {\n335:         ci := &ciList.Items[i]\n336:         result.ScannedCount++\n337:         \n338:         if g.isExpired(ci) {\n339:             result.ExpiredCount++\n340:             if err := g.deleteCodeInterpreter(ctx, namespace, ci.Name); err != nil {\n341:                 result.FailedCount++\n342:                 result.Errors = append(result.Errors, fmt.Sprintf(\"codeinterpreter/%s: %v\", ci.Name, err))\n343:                 klog.ErrorS(err, \"Failed to delete expired codeinterpreter\", \"name\", ci.Name)\n344:             } else {\n345:                 result.DeletedCount++\n346:             }\n347:         }\n348:     }\n349:     \n350:     return nil\n351: }\n352: ```\n353: \n354: ### 5.4 Expiration Detection\n355: \n356: ```go\n357: // isExpired checks if an AgentRuntime is expired.\n358: func (g *GCWorker) isExpired(ar *agentcubev1alpha1.AgentRuntime) bool {\n359:     sandbox := &Sandbox{\n360:         Name:        ar.Name,\n361:         Namespace:   ar.Namespace,\n362:         SessionID:   ar.Labels[\"sessionId\"],\n363:         CreatedAt:   ar.CreationTimestamp.Time,\n364:         LastActivityAt: g.getLastActivityTime(ar),\n365:     }\n366:     \n367:     // Check if being deleted\n368:     if ar.DeletionTimestamp != nil {\n369:         return true\n370:     }\n371:     \n372:     return g.expirationChecker.IsExpired(sandbox)\n373: }\n374: \n375: // isExpired checks if a CodeInterpreter is expired.\n376: func (g *GCWorker) isExpired(ci *agentcubev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter) bool {\n377:     sandbox := &Sandbox{\n378:         Name:        ci.Name,\n379:         Namespace:   ci.Namespace,\n380:         SessionID:   ci.Labels[\"sessionId\"],\n381:         CreatedAt:   ci.CreationTimestamp.Time,\n382:         LastActivityAt: g.getLastActivityTime(ci),\n383:     }\n384:     \n385:     // Check if being deleted\n386:     if ci.DeletionTimestamp != nil {\n387:         return true\n388:     }\n389:     \n390:     return g.expirationChecker.IsExpired(sandbox)\n391: }\n392: \n393: // getLastActivityTime extracts the last activity time from annotations.\n394: func (g *GCWorker) getLastActivityTime(obj metav1.Object) *time.Time {\n395:     annotations := obj.GetAnnotations()\n396:     if annotations == nil {\n397:         return nil\n398:     }\n399:     \n400:     lastActivityStr := annotations[\"last-activity-time\"]\n401:     if lastActivityStr == \"\" {\n402:         return nil\n403:     }\n404:     \n405:     t, err := time.Parse(time.RFC3339, lastActivityStr)\n406:     if err != nil {\n407:         return nil\n408:     }\n409:     \n410:     return &t\n411: }\n412: ```\n413: \n414: ### 5.5 Deletion with Cleanup\n415: \n416: ```go\n417: // deleteAgentRuntime deletes an AgentRuntime and its associated resources.\n418: func (g *GCWorker) deleteAgentRuntime(ctx context.Context, namespace, name string) error {\n419:     // Get the resource to find associated resources\n420:     ar, err := g.client.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Get(ctx, name, metav1.GetOptions{})\n421:     if err != nil {\n422:         if apierrors.IsNotFound(err) {\n423:             return nil // Already deleted\n424:         }\n425:         return err\n426:     }\n427:     \n428:     // Clean up orphaned resources\n429:     sandbox := &Sandbox{\n430:         Name:      ar.Name,\n431:         Namespace: ar.Namespace,\n432:         SessionID: ar.Labels[\"sessionId\"],\n433:     }\n434:     \n435:     if _, err := g.cleanupMgr.CleanupAllResources(ctx, sandbox); err != nil {\n436:         klog.V(2).InfoS(\"Error cleaning up resources\", \"error\", err)\n437:     }\n438:     \n439:     // Delete the resource\n440:     deleteOpts := metav1.DeleteOptions{}\n441:     if g.config.GracePeriod > 0 {\n442:         gracePeriod := int64(g.config.GracePeriod.Seconds())\n443:         deleteOpts.GracePeriodSeconds = &gracePeriod\n444:     }\n445:     \n446:     return g.client.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Delete(ctx, name, deleteOpts)\n447: }\n448: \n449: // deleteCodeInterpreter deletes a CodeInterpreter and its associated resources.\n450: func (g *GCWorker) deleteCodeInterpreter(ctx context.Context, namespace, name string) error {\n451:     // Similar to deleteAgentRuntime\n452:     ci, err := g.client.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(namespace).Get(ctx, name, metav1.GetOptions{})\n453:     if err != nil {\n454:         if apierrors.IsNotFound(err) {\n455:             return nil\n456:         }\n457:         return err\n458:     }\n459:     \n460:     sandbox := &Sandbox{\n461:         Name:      ci.Name,\n462:         Namespace: ci.Namespace,\n463:         SessionID: ci.Labels[\"sessionId\"],\n464:     }\n465:     \n466:     if _, err := g.cleanupMgr.CleanupAllResources(ctx, sandbox); err != nil {\n467:         klog.V(2).InfoS(\"Error cleaning up resources\", \"error\", err)\n468:     }\n469:     \n470:     deleteOpts := metav1.DeleteOptions{}\n471:     if g.config.GracePeriod > 0 {\n472:         gracePeriod := int64(g.config.GracePeriod.Seconds())\n473:         deleteOpts.GracePeriodSeconds = &gracePeriod\n474:     }\n475:     \n476:     return g.client.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(namespace).Delete(ctx, name, deleteOpts)\n477: }\n478: ```\n479: \n480: ### 5.6 Integration with Server\n481: \n482: ```go\n483: // GCServer wraps the GC worker with HTTP handlers.\n484: type GCServer struct {\n485:     worker *GCWorker\n486:     stats  atomic.Value // stores *GCStats\n487: }\n488: \n489: // NewGCServer creates a new GC server.\n490: func NewGCServer(worker *GCWorker) *GCServer {\n491:     gs := &GCServer{\n492:         worker: worker,\n493:     }\n494:     gs.stats.Store(&GCStats{})\n495:     return gs\n496: }\n497: \n498: // RegisterRoutes registers GC routes on the router.\n499: func (gs *GCServer) RegisterRoutes(router *gin.RouterGroup) {\n500:     gc := router.Group(\"/gc\")\n501:     {\n502:         gc.POST(\"/trigger\", gs.handleTrigger)\n503:         gc.GET(\"/status\", gs.handleStatus)\n504:         gc.PUT(\"/config\", gs.handleConfigUpdate)\n505:     }\n506: }\n507: \n508: func (gs *GCServer) handleTrigger(c *gin.Context) {\n509:     select {\n510:     case gs.worker.triggerCh <- struct{}{}:\n511:         c.JSON(http.StatusOK, GCTriggerResponse{\n512:             Started: true,\n513:             Message: \"GC cycle triggered\",\n514:         })\n515:     default:\n516:         c.JSON(http.StatusServiceUnavailable, GCTriggerResponse{\n517:             Started: false,\n518:             Message: \"GC cycle already in progress\",\n519:         })\n520:     }\n521: }\n522: \n523: func (gs *GCServer) handleStatus(c *gin.Context) {\n524:     stats := gs.stats.Load().(*GCStats)\n525:     \n526:     c.JSON(http.StatusOK, GCStatusResponse{\n527:         Running: gs.worker.IsRunning(),\n528:         Config:  gs.worker.GetConfig(),\n529:         Stats:   stats,\n530:     })\n531: }\n532: \n533: func (gs *GCServer) handleConfigUpdate(c *gin.Context) {\n534:     var req GCConfigUpdateRequest\n535:     if err := c.ShouldBindJSON(&req); err != nil {\n536:         c.JSON(http.StatusBadRequest, NewAPIError(err.Error(), \"BadRequest\", http.StatusBadRequest))\n537:         return\n538:     }\n539:     \n540:     gs.worker.UpdateConfig(req)\n541:     \n542:     c.JSON(http.StatusOK, gin.H{\"message\": \"GC configuration updated\"})\n543: }\n544: ```\n545: \n546: ## 6. Error Handling\n547: \n548: ### 6.1 Error Types\n549: \n550: ```go\n551: var (\n552:     ErrGCWorkerNotRunning = errors.New(\"GC worker is not running\")\n553:     ErrGCAlreadyRunning   = errors.New(\"GC cycle already in progress\")\n554:     ErrInvalidConfig      = errors.New(\"invalid GC configuration\")\n555:     ErrNamespaceListFailed = errors.New(\"failed to list namespaces\")\n556: )\n557: ```\n558: \n559: ### 6.2 Error Handling Strategy\n560: \n561: | Scenario | Handling |\n562: |----------|----------|\n563: | Kubernetes API error | Log error, continue with next resource |\n564: | Resource already deleted | Skip, no error |\n565: | Cleanup failure | Log, continue deletion |\n566: | Batch size reached | Stop processing, report partial results |\n567: | Context cancelled | Stop gracefully, record partial results |\n568: \n569: ## 7. Testing Strategy\n570: \n571: ### 7.1 Unit Tests\n572: \n573: ```go\n574: func TestGCWorkerIsExpired(t *testing.T) {\n575:     worker := NewGCWorker(nil, nil, nil)\n576:     \n577:     // Test expired AgentRuntime\n578:     ar := &agentcubev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n579:         ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n580:             Name:              \"test-ar\",\n581:             Namespace:         \"default\",\n582:             CreationTimestamp: metav1.Time{Time: time.Now().Add(-10 * time.Hour)},\n583:             DeletionTimestamp: &metav1.Time{Time: time.Now()},\n584:         },\n585:     }\n586:     \n587:     if !worker.isExpired(ar) {\n588:         t.Error(\"Expected expired AgentRuntime to be marked as expired\")\n589:     }\n590:     \n591:     // Test non-expired AgentRuntime\n592:     ar = &agentcubev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n593:         ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n594:             Name:              \"test-ar-2\",\n595:             Namespace:         \"default\",\n596:             CreationTimestamp: metav1.Time{Time: time.Now()},\n597:         },\n598:     }\n599:     \n600:     if worker.isExpired(ar) {\n601:         t.Error(\"Expected non-expired AgentRuntime to not be marked as expired\")\n602:     }\n603: }\n604: \n605: func TestGCWorkerGetNamespaces(t *testing.T) {\n606:     // Test namespace listing logic\n607: }\n608: \n609: func TestGCConfigValidation(t *testing.T) {\n610:     // Test config validation\n611: }\n612: ```\n613: \n614: ### 7.2 Test Coverage Targets\n615: \n616: | Component | Target Coverage |\n617: |-----------|-----------------|\n618: | gc.go | 80% |\n619: | Integration with cleanup | 75% |\n620: \n621: ## 8. Configuration\n622: \n623: ### 8.1 Environment Variables\n624: \n625: | Variable | Default | Description |\n626: |----------|---------|-------------|\n627: | GC_INTERVAL | 5m | Interval between GC cycles |\n628: | GC_BATCH_SIZE | 50 | Maximum sandboxes processed per cycle |\n629: | GC_MAX_CONCURRENT_DELETES | 10 | Maximum concurrent delete operations |\n630: | GC_GRACE_PERIOD | 30s | Grace period before force delete |\n631: | GC_ENABLED | true | Enable/disable GC worker |\n632: \n633: ### 8.2 Server Configuration Extension\n634: \n635: ```go\n636: type Config struct {\n637:     // ... existing fields ...\n638:     \n639:     // GCConfig is the garbage collection configuration.\n640:     GCConfig *GCConfig\n641: }\n642: ```\n643: \n644: ## 9. Metrics\n645: \n646: ### 9.1 Prometheus Metrics\n647: \n648: | Metric | Type | Description |\n649: |--------|------|-------------|\n650: | gc_cycle_duration_seconds | Histogram | Duration of GC cycle |\n651: | gc_sandboxes_scanned_total | Counter | Total sandboxes scanned |\n652: | gc_sandboxes_expired_total | Counter | Total sandboxes identified as expired |\n653: | gc_sandboxes_deleted_total | Counter | Total sandboxes deleted |\n654: | gc_sandboxes_failed_total | Counter | Total deletion failures |\n655: \n656: ### 9.2 Logging\n657: \n658: | Level | Scenario |\n659: |-------|----------|\n660: | V(4) | GC cycle start/completion |\n661: | V(2) | Individual deletion failures |\n662: | V(1) | Configuration changes |\n663: \n664: ## 10. Dependencies\n665: \n666: ### 10.1 Internal Dependencies\n667: \n668: | Module | Purpose |\n669: |--------|---------|\n670: | github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/client/clientset/versioned | Client for AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter |\n671: | github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager (expiration.go) | Expiration detection |\n672: | github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager (cleanup.go) | Resource cleanup |\n673: \n674: ### 10.2 External Dependencies\n675: \n676: | Package | Purpose |\n677: |---------|---------|\n678: | k8s.io/client-go | Kubernetes client |\n679: | k8s.io/apimachinery | API types |\n680: | k8s.io/klog/v2 | Logging |\n681: | github.com/gin-gonic/gin | HTTP framework |\n682: \n683: ## 11. Security Considerations\n684: \n685: ### 11.1 RBAC Requirements\n686: \n687: ```yaml\n688: rules:\n689: - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n690:   resources: [\"agentruntimes\", \"codeinterpreters\"]\n691:   verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"delete\"]\n692: - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n693:   resources: [\"services\", \"configmaps\", \"persistentvolumeclaims\"]\n694:   verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"delete\"]\n695: - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n696:   resources: [\"namespaces\"]\n697:   verbs: [\"list\", \"get\"]\n698: ```\n699: \n700: ### 11.2 Safety Measures\n701: \n702: - Batch processing prevents overwhelming the API server\n703: - Configurable concurrency limits\n704: - Grace period before force deletion\n705: - Logging of all deletion operations\n706: \n707: ## 12. References\n708: \n709: - [AR-006: Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理](design.md)\n710: - [Expiration Logic](expiration.go)\n711: - [Cleanup Manager](cleanup.go)\n712: - [Kubernetes Garbage Collection](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/cluster-administration/garbage-collection/)\n\n(End of file - total 712 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-008: Sandbox GC 定时清理机制 (Sandbox GC Timing Cleanup Mechanism)\n\n- **AR ID**: AR-008\n- **Module**: pkg/workloadmanager\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: S\n- **Status**: ST-1 Completed\n\n## 1. Overview\n\nThe Sandbox GC (Garbage Collection) mechanism provides automatic periodic cleanup of expired sandboxes in the workloadmanager module. This feature extends the existing expiration logic in `expiration.go` by adding a scheduled GC worker that proactively identifies and removes expired resources, ensuring cluster resources are efficiently managed.\n\n## 2. Architecture\n\n### 2.1 Component Structure\n\n```\npkg/workloadmanager/\n├── client.go              # Kubernetes client initialization (existing)\n├── service.go             # WorkloadManager interface (existing)","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/workloadmanager/design.md","time":{"start":1775846980085,"end":1775846980106}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775846980112,"sessionID":"ses_28745be05ffeTzMz0TdWYlVggx","part":{"id":"prt_d78ba74d70016PEDI4qxEJ12AD","messageID":"msg_d78ba6695001WMDfb24Zgke0Vk","sessionID":"ses_28745be05ffeTzMz0TdWYlVggx","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_e5dbb092c1d9466da735faf0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-008/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-008/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the Sandbox GC (Garbage Collection) timer-based cleanup mechanism in `pkg/workloadmanager`.\n6: \n7: ## Base Specifications\n8: \n9: - **AR**: AR-008\n10: - **Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`\n11: - **Language**: Go\n12: - **Size**: S\n13: - **Base Spec**: client-go library for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## Background\n18: \n19: The workloadmanager module manages Sandboxes (AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter instances). Currently, expiration logic exists in `expiration.go` to determine if a Sandbox is expired based on:\n20: - TTL (Time To Live): 8 hours default\n21: - Idle timeout: 15 minutes default  \n22: - Max lifetime: 24 hours default\n23: - Stale state: Unknown/Failed state for more than 1 hour\n24: \n25: The cleanup logic in `cleanup.go` handles removal of orphaned Kubernetes resources (Services, ConfigMaps, PVCs).\n26: \n27: However, there is no scheduled background process to automatically detect and clean up expired sandboxes. This delta adds a scheduled GC mechanism.\n28: \n29: ---\n30: \n31: ## Requirement: GC Worker Lifecycle\n32: \n33: ### Scenario: GC worker starts on server initialization\n34: \n35: **GIVEN** a WorkloadManager with default GC configuration (GCEnabled=true, GCInterval=5m)\n36: **WHEN** the workloadmanager service starts\n37: **THEN** a background goroutine should start running with a ticker that fires every 5 minutes\n38: \n39: ---\n40: \n41: ### Scenario: GC worker can be disabled via configuration\n42: \n43: **GIVEN** a WorkloadManager with GCEnabled set to false\n44: **WHEN** the workloadmanager service starts\n45: **THEN** no background GC goroutine should be started\n46: \n47: ---\n48: \n49: ### Scenario: GC interval is configurable\n50: \n51: **GIVEN** a WorkloadManager with GCInterval set to 10 minutes\n52: **WHEN** the background GC goroutine runs\n53: **THEN** the ticker should fire every 10 minutes\n54: \n55: ---\n56: \n57: ### Scenario: GC worker stops gracefully on shutdown\n58: \n59: **GIVEN** a running GC background goroutine\n60: **WHEN** the WorkloadManager's Close() method is called\n61: **THEN** the GC goroutine should stop and not process any more sandboxes\n62: \n63: ---\n64: \n65: ## Requirement: Expired Sandbox Detection\n66: \n67: ### Scenario: Detect TTL-expired sandbox\n68: \n69: **GIVEN** a Sandbox with CreatedAt time more than 8 hours ago and no ExpiresAt set\n70: **WHEN** the GC worker runs the isExpired check (expiration.go:isExpiredByTTL)\n71: **THEN** the Sandbox should be identified as expired\n72: \n73: ---\n74: \n75: ### Scenario: Detect idle-timeout expired sandbox\n76: \n77: **GIVEN** a Sandbox with LastActivityAt more than 15 minutes ago\n78: **WHEN** the GC worker runs the isExpired check (expiration.go:isExpiredByIdleTimeout)\n79: **THEN** the Sandbox should be identified as expired\n80: \n81: ---\n82: \n83: ### Scenario: Detect max-lifetime expired sandbox\n84: \n85: **GIVEN** a Sandbox with CreatedAt more than 24 hours ago\n86: **WHEN** the GC worker runs the isExpired check (expiration.go:isExpiredByMaxLifetime)\n87: **THEN** the Sandbox should be identified as expired\n88: \n89: ---\n90: \n91: ### Scenario: Detect stale-state sandbox\n92: \n93: **GIVEN** a Sandbox in state \"Unknown\" or \"Failed\" with CreatedAt more than 1 hour ago\n94: **WHEN** the GC worker runs the isExpired check (expiration.go:isExpiredByStaleState)\n95: **THEN** the Sandbox should be identified as expired\n96: \n97: ---\n98: \n99: ## Requirement: Expired Sandbox Cleanup\n100: \n101: ### Scenario: Delete expired sandbox with default grace period\n102: \n103: **GIVEN** an expired Sandbox\n104: **WHEN** the GC worker triggers deletion\n105: **THEN** the Sandbox should be deleted with a 30-second grace period (default from expiration.go:CalculateGracePeriod)\n106: \n107: ---\n108: \n109: ### Scenario: Force delete stale sandbox\n110: \n111: **GIVEN** a Sandbox in stale state (Unknown/Failed) for more than 1 hour\n112: **WHEN** the GC worker triggers deletion\n113: **THEN** the Sandbox should be force-deleted with GracePeriodSeconds=0\n114: \n115: ---\n116: \n117: ### Scenario: Clean up orphaned Kubernetes resources\n118: \n119: **GIVEN** an expired Sandbox that created K8s resources (Services, ConfigMaps, PVCs)\n120: **WHEN** the cleanup process runs (using cleanup.go:CleanupAllResources)\n121: **THEN** all owned Services, ConfigMaps, and PVCs should be deleted\n122: \n123: ---\n124: \n125: ### Scenario: Skip deletion of retained PVCs\n126: \n127: **GIVEN** an expired Sandbox with an owned PVC backed by a PersistentVolume with ReclaimPolicy=Retain\n128: **WHEN** the cleanup process attempts to delete the PVC\n129: **THEN** the PVC should be skipped and retained\n130: \n131: ---\n132: \n133: ## Requirement: GC Metrics and Logging\n134: \n135: ### Scenario: Log GC cycle results\n136: \n137: **GIVEN** the GC worker running\n138: **WHEN** a GC cycle completes\n139: **THEN** it should log the number of sandboxes scanned and the number cleaned\n140: \n141: ---\n142: \n143: ### Scenario: Log cleanup details per sandbox\n144: \n145: **GIVEN** an expired Sandbox being cleaned up\n146: **WHEN** cleanup completes\n147: **THEN** it should log which resources were cleaned (Service/ConfigMap/PVC names)\n148: \n149: ---\n150: \n151: ## Configuration\n152: \n153: The following configuration options should be available:\n154: \n155: | Field | Type | Default | Description |\n156: |-------|------|---------|-------------|\n157: | GCEnabled | bool | true | Enable/disable GC background worker |\n158: | GCInterval | time.Duration | 5m | Interval between GC cycles |\n159: | GCBatchSize | int | 50 | Max sandboxes to process per cycle |\n160: \n161: ---\n162: \n163: ## Dependencies\n164: \n165: - `expiration.go` - Existing expiration detection logic (isExpired, isExpiredByTTL, isExpiredByIdleTimeout, etc.)\n166: - `cleanup.go` - Existing resource cleanup logic (CleanupManager)\n167: - Uses client-go for K8s operations\n168: \n169: ---\n170: \n171: ## Implementation Notes\n172: \n173: New file to create: `pkg/workloadmanager/gc.go`\n174: \n175: The GC worker should:\n176: 1. Accept a context and stop channel for graceful shutdown\n177: 2. Use a time.Ticker for periodic execution\n178: 3. Call ListSandboxes to get all sandboxes\n179: 4. Filter expired ones using existing isExpired() function\n180: 5. Delete expired sandboxes via WorkloadManager\n181: 6. Clean up orphaned resources using CleanupManager\n182: \n183: ---\n184: \n185: ## Acceptance Criteria\n186: \n187: - [ ] GC background worker starts automatically when workloadmanager starts (if GCEnabled=true)\n188: - [ ] GC can be disabled via configuration (GCEnabled=false)\n189: - [ ] GC interval is configurable (default 5 minutes)\n190: - [ ] GC worker stops gracefully on WorkloadManager Close()\n191: - [ ] All four expiration types (TTL, idle, max lifetime, stale) are correctly detected\n192: - [ ] Expired sandboxes are deleted with appropriate grace period\n193: - [ ] Force deletion (GracePeriodSeconds=0) is used for stale sandboxes\n194: - [ ] Orphaned K8s resources (Services, ConfigMaps, PVCs) are cleaned up\n195: - [ ] PVCs with Retain policy are skipped during cleanup\n196: - [ ] GC cycle results are logged (scanned count, cleaned count)\n197: - [ ] Cleanup details are logged per sandbox\n\n(End of file - total 197 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the Sandbox GC (Garbage Collection) timer-based cleanup mechanism in `pkg/workloadmanager`.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-008\n- **Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: S\n- **Base Spec**: client-go library for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nThe workloadmanager module manages Sandboxes (AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter instances). Currently, expiration logic exists in `expiration.go` to determine if a Sandbox is expired based on:\n- TTL (Time To Live): 8 hours default","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-008/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775846980089,"end":1775846980110}}}}
