{"type":"text","timestamp":1775847016935,"sessionID":"ses_28745be05ffeTzMz0TdWYlVggx","part":{"id":"prt_d78bafc0c001C5gF3EugxDwcs6","messageID":"msg_d78bae0c3001eVlrM7Kup1ut8C","sessionID":"ses_28745be05ffeTzMz0TdWYlVggx","type":"text","text":"## AR-008 Archive Summary\n\n**Completed:**\n- GC worker lifecycle with configurable interval (default 5min)\n- GC enabled/disabled via configuration\n- All four expiration detection types (TTL, idle, max lifetime, stale state)\n- Expired sandbox deletion with 30s grace period\n- Force deletion (GracePeriodSeconds=0) for stale sandboxes\n- Orphaned K8s resource cleanup (Services, ConfigMaps, PVCs)\n- GC statistics tracking and logging\n- `GCHandler` with `TriggerGC()`, `GetStatus()`, `UpdateConfig()` (internal)\n- `ListExpiredSandboxes()` helper function\n\n**Deferred:**\n- HTTP API endpoints (`/api/v1/gc/trigger`, `/api/v1/gc/status`, `/api/v1/gc/config`) — only internal handlers exist, not registered as routes\n- Prometheus metrics (e.g., `gc_cycle_duration_seconds`, `gc_sandboxes_*` counters)\n- Environment variable configuration parsing","time":{"start":1775847016932,"end":1775847016932}}}
